<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c230_20"> 
<div id="v230.20.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H4210 s">, A Psalm</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H3068 s">. The LORD</span><span class="H6030 s"> hear</span><span class="H3117 s"> thee in the day</span><span class="H6869 s"> of trouble</span><span class="H8034 s">; the name</span><span class="H430 s"> of the God</span><span class="H3290 s"> of Jacob</span><span class="H7682 s"> defend</span> thee; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (defend…: Heb. set thee on an high place)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.20.2"><span class="H7971 s">Send</span><span class="H5828 s"> thee help</span><span class="H6944 s"> from the sanctuary</span><span class="H5582 s">, and strengthen</span><span class="H6726 s"> thee out of Zion</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (thee help: Heb. thy help) (strengthen: Heb. support)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.20.3"><span class="H2142 s">Remember</span><span class="H4503 s"> all thy offerings</span><span class="H1878 s">, and accept</span><span class="H5930 s"> thy burnt sacrifice</span><span class="H5542 s">; Selah</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (accept: Heb. turn to ashes: or, make fat)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.20.4"><span class="H5414 s">Grant</span><span class="H3824 s"> thee according to thine own heart</span><span class="H4390 s">, and fulfil</span><span class="H6098 s"> all thy counsel</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.20.5"><span class="H7442 s">We will rejoice</span><span class="H3444 s"> in thy salvation</span><span class="H8034 s">, and in the name</span><span class="H430 s"> of our God</span><span class="H1713 s"> we will set up <i>our</i> banners</span><span class="H3068 s">: the LORD</span><span class="H4390 s"> fulfil</span><span class="H4862 s"> all thy petitions</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.20.6"><span class="H3045 s">Now know</span><span class="H3068 s"> I that the LORD</span><span class="H3467 s"> saveth</span><span class="H4899 s"> his anointed</span><span class="H6030 s">; he will hear</span><span class="H6944 s"> him from his holy</span><span class="H8064 s"> heaven</span><span class="H3468 s"> with the saving</span><span class="H1369 s"> strength</span><span class="H3225 s"> of his right hand</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (his holy…: Heb. the heaven of his holiness) (with…: Heb. by the strength of the salvation of)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.20.7"><span class="H7393 s">Some <i>trust</i> in chariots</span><span class="H5483 s">, and some in horses</span><span class="H2142 s">: but we will remember</span><span class="H8034 s"> the name</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> our God</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.20.8"><span class="H3766 s">They are brought down</span><span class="H5307 s"> and fallen</span><span class="H6965 s">: but we are risen</span><span class="H5749 s">, and stand upright</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.20.9"><span class="H3467 s">Save</span><span class="H3068 s">, LORD</span><span class="H4428 s">: let the king</span><span class="H6030 s"> hear</span><span class="H3117 s"> us when</span><span class="H7121 s"> we call</span>.</div></div>

